WEBVTT

00:02.043 --> 00:05.380
- ♪

00:05.463 --> 00:08.090
- Hey, check it out, guys.
The team's hoodies are here.

00:08.173 --> 00:10.427
- Oh, great.

00:10.510 --> 00:12.637
- Here you go, Newt.
- Ooh.

00:12.721 --> 00:15.265
- And Troy.
- Thank you.

00:15.348 --> 00:16.474
- I love this embroidery.

00:16.558 --> 00:21.396
The cross-stitching really
makes my name look "gangsta."

00:21.479 --> 00:24.190
- Hey, this feels
a little small.

00:24.274 --> 00:25.775
- SOPHIE: [laughing]

00:25.859 --> 00:27.694
- That's because I had Bella
order it in my size.

00:27.777 --> 00:30.447
Team sweatshirts
are really for girlfriends.

00:30.530 --> 00:31.948
- Well, uh, I had them do

00:32.031 --> 00:33.616
something a little
special with mine.

00:33.700 --> 00:35.201
Instead of just
writing "Troy,"

00:35.285 --> 00:36.661
I had them write "The Troy,"

00:36.745 --> 00:40.957
you know, to...to stand
out from you guys.

00:41.040 --> 00:42.917
- You definitely
stand out--

00:43.001 --> 00:44.961
'cause it says "Then Troy."

00:45.044 --> 00:47.172
- Aw, man!

00:47.255 --> 00:48.089
How could they make
this mistake?

00:48.173 --> 00:51.134
Who thinks someone's
name is "Then"?

00:51.217 --> 00:53.636
- Who thinks someone's
name is "The"?

00:53.720 --> 00:55.263
- OTHERS: [laughing]

00:55.346 --> 00:56.806
- Maybe it's your new thing.

00:56.890 --> 00:59.476
"Then Troy" realized
his hoodie was messed up.

00:59.559 --> 01:00.977
- OTHERS: [laughing]
- Hey!

01:01.060 --> 01:03.271
- "Then Troy"
got embarrassed.

01:03.354 --> 01:05.355
- OTHERS: [laughing]
- Embarrassed?

01:05.440 --> 01:07.358
The Troy does not
get embarrassed, okay?

01:07.442 --> 01:09.611
- "Then Troy" looked like
he was gonna cry.

01:09.694 --> 01:12.238
- OTHERS: Aww...
- Ha. Ha. I get it.

01:12.322 --> 01:14.199
"Then Troy" told...

01:14.282 --> 01:16.117
"Then Friends"...

01:16.201 --> 01:17.786
rude!

01:20.121 --> 01:21.915
- I'd better go--
I've gotta get up early

01:21.998 --> 01:23.374
to work at my family's stand
at the farmers' market.

01:23.458 --> 01:26.628
- Ooh, maybe I'll drop by.
I love the farmers' market.

01:26.711 --> 01:28.797
- Oh, me, too.
- The locally-grown produce.

01:28.880 --> 01:30.340
- The deep-fried food truck.
- The friendly farmers.

01:30.423 --> 01:33.384
- The deep-fried food truck.
- Fresh-squeezed juice.

01:33.468 --> 01:35.845
- The deep-fried food truck.

01:35.929 --> 01:37.514
- It'd be healthier

01:37.597 --> 01:40.850
to get hit by that truck
than to eat from it.

01:40.934 --> 01:43.853
- Oh, I'll see ya tomorrow.
Pepper's helping at the stand.

01:43.937 --> 01:47.232
- And I can't wait.
[laughing]

01:47.315 --> 01:49.692
You have to save me!
- What do you mean?

01:49.776 --> 01:51.778
- I don't like
working at the stand.

01:51.861 --> 01:53.488
I have to smile at strangers,

01:53.571 --> 01:55.448
and pretend I know
stuff about vegetables.

01:55.532 --> 01:57.116
I don't know the difference

01:57.200 --> 01:59.202
between a scallion
and a green onion.

01:59.285 --> 02:01.037
- They're the same thing.

02:01.120 --> 02:04.082
- See? That's why
I need you.

02:04.165 --> 02:06.167
Please keep me company.

02:06.251 --> 02:07.377
- Sure, I can come hang out.

02:07.460 --> 02:08.294
I don't think I have
anything planned.

02:08.377 --> 02:10.713
- Pinky promise?
- Yeah, pinky promise.

02:10.797 --> 02:12.465
- Yay! [laughing]
It's gonna be so fun.

02:12.549 --> 02:14.551
Just a few things
to remember.

02:14.634 --> 02:16.845
Uh, bring old clothes,
wear sunscreen,

02:16.928 --> 02:19.556
and show up at 4:00 a.m.
- Did you say 4:00 a.m.?

02:19.639 --> 02:22.767
- Pinky promises
are legally binding.

02:22.851 --> 02:26.813
- ♪

02:26.896 --> 02:28.147
- ♪ You won't find
me in the bleachers ♪

02:28.231 --> 02:30.358
- ♪ Yeah that girl
is one of us ♪

02:30.441 --> 02:32.360
- ♪ I'm made of spice
and sugar ♪

02:32.443 --> 02:33.236
- ♪ She's pretty...
she's pretty tough ♪

02:33.319 --> 02:35.238
- ♪ Then add
a little glitter ♪

02:35.321 --> 02:36.114
{\an8}- ♪ She off in
a cloud of dust ♪

02:36.197 --> 02:38.741
{\an8}- ♪ And you get...
you get... ♪

02:38.825 --> 02:40.410
{\an8}- ♪ A game changer,
play maker ♪

02:40.493 --> 02:41.744
{\an8}♪ Take the ball,
she'll see ya later ♪

02:41.828 --> 02:43.580
{\an8}- ♪ I'm on a dreamlike,
teamlike ♪

02:43.663 --> 02:45.582
{\an8}♪ Livin' like
one of the boys ♪

02:45.665 --> 02:48.501
{\an8}- ♪ She got it goin', goin',
she got it goin' on ♪

02:48.585 --> 02:49.752
{\an8}- ♪ Play like Friday night ♪

02:49.836 --> 02:51.546
{\an8}♪ Kickin' like
one of the boys ♪

02:51.629 --> 02:54.507
{\an8}- ♪ She got it goin', goin',
she got it goin' on ♪

02:54.591 --> 02:56.217
{\an8}- ♪ One of the boys ♪♪

03:00.430 --> 03:06.269
- ♪

03:06.352 --> 03:08.187
{\an8}- [laughing]

03:08.271 --> 03:10.273
{\an8}This looks like
my Aunt Carol.

03:10.356 --> 03:11.274
{\an8}- This one's your mom.

03:11.357 --> 03:13.151
{\an8}Hey, Carol, did you watch
the new episode of

03:13.234 --> 03:15.945
{\an8}"Bring Me a Bachelor"
last night?

03:16.029 --> 03:18.031
{\an8}- I never miss it, Jan.

03:18.114 --> 03:21.117
{\an8}- Come on, this is
a Huggins stand.

03:21.200 --> 03:23.995
{\an8}Our gourds watch manly
programmin' like

03:24.078 --> 03:26.205
{\an8}"Ice Road Tractor Disasters."

03:26.289 --> 03:27.540
{\an8}Hmph.

03:27.624 --> 03:30.418
{\an8}- I know at least
one Huggins who watches

03:30.501 --> 03:32.462
{\an8}"Bring Me a Bachelor."

03:32.545 --> 03:33.463
- Pepper.

03:33.546 --> 03:37.133
She's...she's talkin'
about my Uncle Fred.

03:37.216 --> 03:39.385
- [cell phone buzzing]
- Oh.

03:39.469 --> 03:40.386
Oh, Charlie's gonna
be here any minute.

03:40.470 --> 03:42.889
I'm gonna go meet him
in the parking lot.

03:42.972 --> 03:44.599
- Wait. Charlie?

03:44.682 --> 03:47.477
As in Sawyer's awful
Cousin Charlie?

03:47.560 --> 03:48.937
I don't wanna see him.

03:49.020 --> 03:50.313
- Why not?

03:50.396 --> 03:52.649
- It was Sawyer's
ninth birthday party.

03:52.732 --> 03:54.275
I was trying to avoid
Troy and the other boys

03:54.359 --> 03:57.362
who were having a...
- LITTLE TROY: Food fight!

03:57.445 --> 03:59.030
- [food thwacking]

03:59.113 --> 03:59.989
- Then Charlie walked over.

04:00.073 --> 04:02.825
- Hey, Bella,
this is for you.

04:02.909 --> 04:05.453
- [liquid splatters]

04:05.536 --> 04:06.829
- OLDER BELLA: And out of
literally nowhere,

04:06.913 --> 04:08.957
poured a smoothie all over
my brand new party dress.

04:09.040 --> 04:11.292
- OTHER KIDS:
[laughing]

04:11.376 --> 04:15.171
- Do you think
this is funny--Chuckles?

04:15.254 --> 04:16.839
OLDER BELLA:
Everyone laughed at me.

04:16.923 --> 04:18.966
I'll never forget
how embarrassed I was.

04:19.050 --> 04:21.010
- Oh, Bella,
that's terrible.

04:21.094 --> 04:22.971
- I know. Let's not
talk to him.

04:23.054 --> 04:23.888
I say we totally
ice him out.

04:23.972 --> 04:26.724
- I got your back, baby.

04:26.808 --> 04:28.101
Here they come.

04:28.184 --> 04:30.728
- Bella, you remember
my Cousin Charlie, right?

04:33.106 --> 04:35.191
- Uh...uh...

04:35.274 --> 04:36.359
[laughing]

04:36.442 --> 04:38.695
- What happened to
icing him out?

04:38.778 --> 04:41.364
- I melted.
He's way too hot.

04:43.908 --> 04:46.327
[laughing]

04:46.411 --> 04:48.913
- VENDOR: Thank you for
your business. Enjoy.

04:48.997 --> 04:50.164
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

04:50.248 --> 04:52.709
- How can you guys
eat that stuff?

04:52.792 --> 04:54.711
It's so bad for you.

04:54.794 --> 04:57.463
- [sipping, gagging]
Delicious.

04:57.547 --> 04:59.215
- Yeah, well, I wanna marry

04:59.298 --> 05:00.299
this deep-fried
beef on a stick.

05:00.383 --> 05:03.302
- "Then Troy" kissed
his deep-fried bride

05:03.386 --> 05:05.471
and they lived
happily ever after.

05:05.555 --> 05:07.056
- Until he got
hungry one night.

05:07.140 --> 05:09.142
"Then Troy" was single again.

05:09.225 --> 05:10.184
- SOPHIE &amp; NEWT:
[laughing]

05:10.268 --> 05:13.563
- This beef is so good.
[sniffing]

05:13.646 --> 05:16.107
I can't even be
mad right now.

05:16.190 --> 05:19.736
- [chick chirping]

05:19.819 --> 05:22.572
- Look who I found.

05:22.655 --> 05:25.074
Aw, with a spot
on your head.

05:25.158 --> 05:26.784
Aw, hi, Spot.

05:26.868 --> 05:28.703
- I knew under that
tough exterior

05:28.786 --> 05:30.413
there was a big,
old softie.

05:30.496 --> 05:33.249
- Please. I just don't want
it to get stepped on.

05:33.332 --> 05:34.834
- Yeah, right, softie.

05:34.917 --> 05:36.461
♪ You love him ♪

05:36.544 --> 05:38.087
- NEWT: She does.

05:38.171 --> 05:40.006
She's capable of love.

05:40.089 --> 05:41.758
And hate.

05:41.841 --> 05:43.760
- Yeah, well, we'd better
take Spot here

05:43.843 --> 05:46.095
back to the Schweger Farm's
petting zoo.

05:46.179 --> 05:47.722
- Well, you have
fun with that.

05:47.805 --> 05:50.933
I'm gonna get
a second breakfast.

05:51.017 --> 05:54.729
- Hey, uh, you hungry?
- [chick chirping]

05:54.812 --> 05:58.107
- Oh, no, he probably
knew this guy.

05:58.191 --> 05:59.734
I'm sorry.

05:59.817 --> 06:05.698
- ♪

06:05.782 --> 06:07.617
- Wow.

06:07.700 --> 06:09.452
Charlie is a total
dream bae.

06:09.535 --> 06:10.953
- I know. Right?

06:11.037 --> 06:12.789
Too bad he's probably
still a jerk.

06:12.872 --> 06:13.915
- He doesn't seem
like a jerk.

06:13.998 --> 06:15.958
- Oh, yeah?

06:16.042 --> 06:17.460
Just look at
him over there

06:17.543 --> 06:20.797
taking food from that
helpless old lady.

06:20.880 --> 06:23.007
- Yeah, Bella, and maybe
after he helps her

06:23.091 --> 06:24.759
load that food in her car,

06:24.842 --> 06:26.803
he'll steal all
of her purse candy.

06:26.886 --> 06:29.305
- Fine! There's
nothing wrong with him.

06:29.388 --> 06:31.599
He's hot and helpful.
- Yeah.

06:31.682 --> 06:34.602
I wish my boyfriend
was that helpful.

06:34.685 --> 06:36.145
- Ah! [smacks hand]

06:36.229 --> 06:37.939
Only two samples
per person.

06:38.022 --> 06:39.774
We talked about
this, Jeremy.

06:43.277 --> 06:44.320
- Oh, Sawyer...

06:44.403 --> 06:46.823
- I'm sorry.
Did you say something?

06:46.906 --> 06:49.367
I was just watching Charlie
carry a box of muscles--

06:49.450 --> 06:51.327
I...I mean abs.
Apples!

06:51.410 --> 06:52.829
I mean apples!
- PEPPER: [laughing]

06:52.912 --> 06:55.498
- Bells, you are
spazzing hard.

06:55.581 --> 06:57.708
- Yeah.

06:57.792 --> 06:59.877
'Cause I think
I'm crushing hard.

06:59.961 --> 07:01.712
- You and Charlie?

07:01.796 --> 07:04.507
Oh, my, cousins!
I love it!

07:04.590 --> 07:06.050
- I know.

07:06.134 --> 07:08.136
I just need to figure out
a way to talk to him--

07:08.219 --> 07:09.178
using actual words.

07:09.262 --> 07:12.181
I...uh...guh...uh...buh...

07:12.265 --> 07:13.391
What was that?

07:13.474 --> 07:14.308
- You need to get a grip
and make your move--

07:14.392 --> 07:15.977
otherwise,
someone else will.

07:16.060 --> 07:18.855
- Rules are rules.

07:18.938 --> 07:21.983
Now get along.
Get. Get. Go on.

07:22.066 --> 07:24.735
- It might be me.

07:26.779 --> 07:28.531
- [sighing]
I'm gonna do it.

07:28.614 --> 07:30.700
I'm gonna make a move.

07:30.783 --> 07:32.285
So, what's the plan?
Hit me with it.

07:32.368 --> 07:34.704
- You're gonna go
home and change.

07:34.787 --> 07:37.206
- Got it. Then what?
- That's it. You need to change.

07:37.290 --> 07:39.167
All of this.
Like all of it.

07:39.250 --> 07:41.794
Now go.
[laughing]

07:41.878 --> 07:46.924
- ♪

07:47.008 --> 07:48.885
- FEMALE VENDOR: Thank you
so much. Enjoy.

07:48.968 --> 07:50.428
- Thank you.

07:50.511 --> 07:52.221
Oh, you know,
for a double-fried

07:52.305 --> 07:54.223
bacon-wrapped asparagus,
this is surprisingly fresh.

07:54.307 --> 07:55.766
- It should be.

07:55.850 --> 07:57.602
You know, most of
our ingredients

07:57.685 --> 07:59.562
come right from
Schweger Farms.

07:59.645 --> 08:01.105
- Wait, Schweger Farms?

08:01.189 --> 08:03.441
You mean the farm that
runs the petting zoo?

08:03.524 --> 08:05.443
- Yep, they're our
biggest supplier.

08:05.526 --> 08:07.111
- [timer dings]
- Oh.

08:07.195 --> 08:10.114
Chicken strips are up!
- Where's the chick?

08:10.198 --> 08:12.408
- We returned it to the petting
zoo right before they closed.

08:12.491 --> 08:14.410
- Oh, no.
- I knew it.

08:14.493 --> 08:16.871
♪ You love him ♪
- I don't love him!

08:16.954 --> 08:19.916
I just don't want us to be
accessories to chicken murder.

08:19.999 --> 08:21.459
- I'm confused.
- I'm scared.

08:21.542 --> 08:24.128
- I just found out
that Schweger Farms

08:24.212 --> 08:26.255
sells their chicks to the
farmers in the fryer truck.

08:26.339 --> 08:27.882
We've gotta get Spot back.

08:27.965 --> 08:29.592
- Are you crazy?
This is Texas.

08:29.675 --> 08:31.260
You could go to jail
for chicken theft.

08:31.344 --> 08:32.803
Just ask Sawyer's
Uncle Fred--

08:32.886 --> 08:36.097
any Saturday during visiting
hours at the county jail.

08:36.182 --> 08:37.642
- Well, if we don't
do something fast,

08:37.725 --> 08:38.601
Spot can end up deep-fried.

08:38.683 --> 08:40.895
- TROY: Mmmm, deep-fried.
- NEWT: I'm in.

08:40.977 --> 08:43.940
- I'm sorry, that was my stomach
talking, not my conscience.

08:44.023 --> 08:45.942
I'm in. Let's do it.

08:46.025 --> 08:51.948
- ♪

08:52.031 --> 08:53.616
- Okay, Sawyer,
full disclosure--

08:53.699 --> 08:55.409
you might notice
I look different.

08:55.493 --> 08:56.953
- Weren't you wearing
this earlier?

08:57.036 --> 08:59.747
- Know what? Carry on.
- Yeah.

08:59.830 --> 09:01.374
- You look great, Bella.

09:01.457 --> 09:03.376
Charlie's gonna
be so blown away,

09:03.459 --> 09:05.127
he'll have a massive
heart attack

09:05.211 --> 09:06.754
and drop dead on the spot.

09:06.837 --> 09:07.505
- Oh, I hope he does!

09:07.588 --> 09:09.173
Not the dying
part, though.

09:09.257 --> 09:11.300
Or the heart attack part.

09:11.384 --> 09:13.636
But the "blown away" part.

09:13.719 --> 09:16.180
- Here he comes.

09:18.557 --> 09:21.102
- Hey, Sawyer,
can you give me a hand?

09:21.185 --> 09:23.646
- Sorry, I'm pretty busy
dishin' out sample-sized--

09:23.729 --> 09:25.439
Hey, man, get outta here!
[smacking hand]

09:25.523 --> 09:27.567
- Yeah, Pepper,
help him with that.

09:27.650 --> 09:28.943
- Try not to scream
when Charlie says "Yes."

09:29.026 --> 09:31.112
Just give it a cute giggle.
- [giggling coyly]

09:31.195 --> 09:33.072
- Perfect.

09:38.494 --> 09:40.162
- Okay.

09:40.246 --> 09:44.041
Here we go.

09:44.125 --> 09:45.459
So, uh, do you have
any big plans

09:45.543 --> 09:48.379
after the farmers'
market today?

09:48.462 --> 09:49.839
- No, not really.

09:49.922 --> 09:52.550
- Cool. Cool. Cool.

09:52.633 --> 09:55.720
Uh, how do you feel
about ice cream?

09:55.803 --> 09:58.514
- I like it.
- Me, too. Me, too.

09:58.597 --> 10:03.394
Do you wanna get
ice cream after this?

10:03.477 --> 10:04.770
Together?

10:04.854 --> 10:07.023
- Do you mean like a date?

10:07.106 --> 10:09.734
- Yeah, I do.

10:09.817 --> 10:12.611
- Oh. No, thanks.

10:12.695 --> 10:15.156
- [giggling coyly]
Wait. What?

10:15.239 --> 10:18.534
- Sorry, Bella,
I'm not interested.

10:18.617 --> 10:21.829
I think you know why.

10:21.912 --> 10:23.581
- But...

10:23.664 --> 10:25.791
I don't know why.

10:25.875 --> 10:29.211
- I just figured out what
looks different about you.

10:29.295 --> 10:31.088
You look way sadder.

10:31.172 --> 10:32.757
Yeah.

10:37.470 --> 10:44.226
- ♪

10:44.310 --> 10:46.395
- Talk to me, Bella.

10:46.479 --> 10:49.607
- [muffled gibberish]

10:49.690 --> 10:52.818
- Okay, let's try
that again.

10:52.902 --> 10:54.445
- I'm just so embarrassed.

10:54.528 --> 10:55.946
Being rejected
was bad enough,

10:56.030 --> 10:58.741
but I have no idea
what Charlie meant by,

10:58.824 --> 11:00.076
"You know why."

11:00.159 --> 11:02.661
I went through all
the possibilities in my head.

11:02.745 --> 11:04.830
Do I smell? Nope.
I did a pit check.

11:04.914 --> 11:07.166
[sniffing]
Twice.

11:07.249 --> 11:08.501
Maybe I was wrong.
Can...can you?

11:08.584 --> 11:10.503
- PEPPER: [gasping]

11:10.586 --> 11:12.963
Sorry, Bella, but even
our friendship has its limits.

11:13.047 --> 11:16.467
- I don't get it.
I was nothing but nice.

11:16.550 --> 11:17.968
Plus, when we were
little kids,

11:18.052 --> 11:19.095
Charlie was a jerk to me.

11:19.178 --> 11:22.598
If anyone should "know why,"
he should "know why."

11:22.681 --> 11:24.016
- Aw...

11:24.100 --> 11:26.435
Maybe you were too much
for him done up like this--

11:26.519 --> 11:28.104
a little too high
maintenance.

11:28.187 --> 11:30.773
- Pepper, you're the one who
told me to get dressed up.

11:30.856 --> 11:33.359
- Yeah, that's my bad.

11:33.442 --> 11:34.693
- It's like Charlie has
something against me.

11:34.777 --> 11:37.488
Do you think Sawyer
knows what it is?

11:37.571 --> 11:39.115
- Let's ask him.

11:39.198 --> 11:40.449
Sawyer, get outta
the refrigerator

11:40.533 --> 11:42.785
and come in here, please.

11:42.868 --> 11:45.496
- Are you done with
your "girlie" emergency?

11:45.579 --> 11:47.289
I wanna go.

11:47.373 --> 11:51.502
Our...movie...
starts in five minutes.

11:51.585 --> 11:53.462
- Not yet.
I need your help.

11:53.546 --> 11:54.964
- But the movie!

11:55.047 --> 11:56.966
- We can watch "Bring Me
a Bachelor" later, Sawyer.

11:57.049 --> 11:58.968
- Nah, I don't watch that.
[laughing]

11:59.051 --> 12:00.553
But if your mom spoils
it again for me,

12:00.636 --> 12:03.347
I'm gonna be mad.

12:03.431 --> 12:04.974
- Okay, I need to know...

12:05.057 --> 12:08.477
does Charlie have a problem
with me for some reason?

12:08.561 --> 12:10.563
- Oh, most definitely.
Problem solved. Let's go.

12:10.646 --> 12:13.065
- No, okay,
what do you mean

12:13.149 --> 12:15.693
Charlie most definitely
has a problem with me?

12:15.776 --> 12:17.403
- I think you know
why, Bella.

12:17.486 --> 12:20.322
- I do not know why!
- Tell her why!

12:20.406 --> 12:21.907
- Okay.

12:21.991 --> 12:24.660
It happened at
my ninth birthday party.

12:24.743 --> 12:26.495
I was about to walk out
with my cake...

12:26.579 --> 12:28.080
That thing was amazin'.

12:28.164 --> 12:31.417
It was shaped like a hot dog,
but it was actually a cake.

12:31.500 --> 12:33.836
The mustard was lemon,
the ketchup was raspberry, and--

12:33.919 --> 12:35.337
- I do not care about
your hot dog cake!

12:35.421 --> 12:36.964
- Focus, Sawyer!

12:37.047 --> 12:39.175
- Fine. Like I was saying...

12:39.258 --> 12:41.427
I was walking out
when I heard Bella.

12:41.510 --> 12:42.887
- LITTLE BELLA:
This is the worst party ever!

12:42.970 --> 12:46.724
I'm leaving!

12:46.807 --> 12:47.766
- Where's everyone going?

12:47.850 --> 12:52.188
- Bella left
and everyone went with her.

12:52.271 --> 12:54.315
- What a fun killer.

12:54.398 --> 12:57.568
Who's gonna help me
eat the hot dog?

12:57.651 --> 13:00.738
We were mad at you
for years.

13:00.821 --> 13:01.906
I got over it eventually.

13:01.989 --> 13:03.282
But I guess
Charlie didn't.

13:03.365 --> 13:05.284
He was real excited
about that hot dog cake.

13:05.367 --> 13:08.204
That guy has
his priorities straight.

13:08.287 --> 13:10.581
- But the only reason
I left was because

13:10.664 --> 13:12.958
Charlie dumped
a smoothie on me.

13:13.042 --> 13:14.084
- It was a Huggins
party, Bella.

13:14.168 --> 13:18.130
Food fights are mandatory
and you were a fun killer.

13:18.214 --> 13:19.632
- A fun killer?
- Mm-hm.

13:19.715 --> 13:22.927
- No way.
I'm a fun starter.

13:23.010 --> 13:24.220
Right, Pepper?

13:24.303 --> 13:25.554
- So much fun.

13:25.638 --> 13:28.307
All the time.

13:28.390 --> 13:31.143
- Yeah, well, that's not
what Charlie thinks.

13:31.227 --> 13:32.478
- Fine.

13:32.561 --> 13:35.022
I'm going to show Charlie
how awesome I can be.

13:35.105 --> 13:36.899
I'll just go back to
the farm stand tomorrow

13:36.982 --> 13:38.692
as my funnest fun self.

13:38.776 --> 13:41.570
Fun Bella is comin'
out to play.

13:41.654 --> 13:43.405
- [laughing]

13:43.489 --> 13:45.574
That's one of
my favorite Bellas.

13:45.658 --> 13:47.117
- [cell phone buzzing]

13:47.201 --> 13:49.745
- And that's your mom spoiling
"Bring Me a Bachelor."

13:49.828 --> 13:51.163
Looks like Emily
chose Brock.

13:51.247 --> 13:53.499
Oh.

13:53.582 --> 13:55.125
Thanks a lot, Jan.

13:55.209 --> 14:05.719
- ♪

14:07.596 --> 14:10.391
- Okay, come on.
- Thank you.

14:10.474 --> 14:13.102
- Thank you. Thank you.
Thank you.

14:13.185 --> 14:17.690
Whoa, aren't you kids a little
old for the petting zoo?

14:17.773 --> 14:19.817
- Uh, we're tall
for our age.

14:19.900 --> 14:21.026
- It's a glandular thing.

14:21.110 --> 14:23.028
- And...and shame on you
for pointin' that out.

14:23.112 --> 14:27.199
Rude.
- Sorry.

14:27.283 --> 14:28.617
- All right, look for Spot.

14:28.701 --> 14:31.370
He's the one with
the...spot.

14:31.453 --> 14:33.622
- Right.
- Right.

14:33.706 --> 14:35.457
- [chicks chirping]

14:35.541 --> 14:36.917
- Hey, I don't see him.

14:37.001 --> 14:39.378
- Sophie, I have a visual.

14:39.461 --> 14:42.464
- [Spot chirping]

14:42.548 --> 14:43.841
- Hey. Hi, here.

14:43.924 --> 14:45.551
Can I have a turn
holding the chick?

14:45.634 --> 14:48.304
- I don't know.
Can you?

14:48.387 --> 14:49.471
- Sure can.

14:49.555 --> 14:51.557
- [Spot chirping]

14:51.640 --> 14:55.019
- Got him. Let's go.

14:55.102 --> 14:57.146
Guys, what's the hold up?

14:57.229 --> 15:00.524
- We can't leave without Chirpy,
Bubblegum, Geoffrey,

15:00.608 --> 15:03.319
Joffrey and Kanye.

15:03.402 --> 15:05.362
- Fine. We'll save 'em all.

15:05.446 --> 15:07.823
But only because I don't
wanna watch you guys cry.

15:07.906 --> 15:11.410
- Thank you.

15:11.493 --> 15:14.163
- Hey, friends!
Where's the party?

15:14.246 --> 15:16.332
Oh, wait.
She just got here.

15:16.415 --> 15:18.834
And so did these
donuts. Boom!

15:18.917 --> 15:21.003
- Oh, nice!

15:21.086 --> 15:25.549
- Time to show Charlie
I am no fun killer.

15:25.633 --> 15:27.551
- Donuts?
[laughing]

15:27.635 --> 15:29.261
Bella, you are so fun!

15:29.345 --> 15:31.221
Bella, you're just
so fun, right?

15:31.305 --> 15:32.473
Oh, Sawyer and I need to
go and do something.

15:32.556 --> 15:34.558
Bella, can you help
Charlie watch the stand?

15:34.642 --> 15:37.061
- Sure, I'll help
Charlie watch the stand.

15:37.144 --> 15:39.063
- Okay, what do
we need to do?

15:39.146 --> 15:42.191
- Nothing.
Bella likes Charlie.

15:42.274 --> 15:45.444
- Aw, we could have
a double wedding.

15:45.527 --> 15:48.614
I really need to stop
watching "Bring Me a Bachelor."

15:48.697 --> 15:50.699
Sorry.

15:50.783 --> 15:52.117
- Oh. Hey, Charlie.

15:52.201 --> 15:53.869
You know what would
be a lot of fun?

15:53.952 --> 15:55.871
A pumpkin drum solo.

15:55.954 --> 15:57.956
[imitates drumming]

15:58.040 --> 15:59.750
Thank you, farmers' market!

15:59.833 --> 16:01.877
Oh!

16:01.960 --> 16:03.879
- Hey, thanks for
the donuts,

16:03.962 --> 16:05.089
but you don't
have to stick around.

16:05.172 --> 16:07.883
Business is slow this morning.
- Oh, really?

16:07.966 --> 16:09.885
Well, I can do
something about that.

16:09.968 --> 16:12.096
- Come to the Huggins
Family Farm stand

16:12.179 --> 16:14.056
where the produce
is delicious

16:14.139 --> 16:15.766
and the entertainment
is free.

16:15.849 --> 16:17.893
- Hey, watch it!

16:17.976 --> 16:20.562
- Sorry. Here.
Have one on the house.

16:20.646 --> 16:22.147
- Ow!

16:22.231 --> 16:24.441
- She's new.

16:24.525 --> 16:27.152
Same old Bella.

16:28.404 --> 16:30.739
I have you, farmers' market!

16:30.823 --> 16:35.411
- ♪

16:35.494 --> 16:36.537
- TROY: Hee. Hee
Hee. Hee. Ho. Ho.

16:36.620 --> 16:39.915
- Troy, I'm gonna need you
to giggle in your head.

16:39.998 --> 16:41.750
- I can't help it.
It's tickling me.

16:41.834 --> 16:45.295
Hee. Hee. Hee. Hee.
Sorry. Under control.

16:45.379 --> 16:47.965
- All right,
let's do this.

16:48.048 --> 16:50.008
Sweet, we're in the clear.

16:50.092 --> 16:53.429
- Morning, Mr. Schweger.
- Oh, howdy, Sawyer.

16:53.512 --> 16:57.266
- Of course, Sawyer knows
every farmer in the state.

16:57.349 --> 17:01.311
- Aren't you guys a little
old for the petting zoo?

17:01.395 --> 17:03.063
- Was Jane Goodall
a little old

17:03.147 --> 17:05.983
to live with those
chimpanzees, Pepper?

17:06.066 --> 17:06.900
- Hee. Hee. Hee.

17:06.983 --> 17:09.569
Hey, man, stop it.
Quit playin'.

17:09.653 --> 17:11.989
- Hey, have you got
my chick in your pocket?

17:12.071 --> 17:14.157
- Uh, no, that's crazy.

17:14.241 --> 17:16.785
- Guys, why are you stealing
the Schwegers' chickens.

17:16.868 --> 17:20.289
You can go to jail for
that--like my Uncle Fred.

17:20.372 --> 17:23.625
- We're not stealing them.
We're liberating them.

17:23.709 --> 17:26.795
- Yeah, come on, go!

17:26.878 --> 17:29.590
Run! Go! Go on!

17:29.673 --> 17:32.843
Go! Run! Be free!

17:32.926 --> 17:35.220
Go! Come on.

17:35.304 --> 17:36.638
I can't help you,
if you can't help yourself.

17:36.722 --> 17:39.057
Meet me half way.

17:39.141 --> 17:40.684
- What's going on?

17:40.768 --> 17:42.311
- When these chicks grow up,

17:42.394 --> 17:44.188
he sells them to
the farmer's fryer truck.

17:44.271 --> 17:46.148
- No, I don't.
- Oh, really?

17:46.231 --> 17:49.318
The fryer truck lady said you're
their biggest supplier.

17:49.401 --> 17:52.488
- Yes, of vegetables.

17:52.571 --> 17:54.490
They love my asparagus.

17:54.573 --> 17:57.034
- Well, if you're
a vegetable farm,

17:57.117 --> 17:58.535
why do you have
a petting zoo?

17:58.619 --> 18:01.121
- Because no one likes
to pet vegetables.

18:01.205 --> 18:04.041
- Well, you haven't
met my Uncle Fred.

18:04.124 --> 18:06.668
- But then...

18:06.752 --> 18:09.254
Oh, I get it.

18:09.338 --> 18:10.506
Sorry about that.

18:10.589 --> 18:13.342
- It's okay, but I am gonna
need the chicks back.

18:13.425 --> 18:15.177
- Yeah, no problem.

18:15.260 --> 18:17.429
Uh, well...

18:17.513 --> 18:19.681
I guess this
is goodbye, Spot.

18:19.765 --> 18:20.641
I love you!

18:20.724 --> 18:23.018
- I knew it.

18:23.101 --> 18:25.020
- Then Sophie admitted
she had a heart.

18:25.103 --> 18:28.190
- Really, guys? I'm trying to
have a moment with my chick.

18:28.273 --> 18:30.901
- Hee. Hee. Hee.
Hee. Hee. Hee.

18:30.984 --> 18:32.694
Hee. Hee. Hee.

18:32.778 --> 18:34.863
Oops, I missed one.

18:34.947 --> 18:39.535
- ♪

18:39.618 --> 18:41.245
- You know what, Charlie?

18:41.328 --> 18:43.205
I know you think
I'm a fun killer.

18:43.288 --> 18:45.249
But I'm not
the fun killer--you are.

18:45.332 --> 18:46.125
- Fun killer?

18:46.208 --> 18:48.877
What...what are
you talking about?

18:48.961 --> 18:50.546
- Sawyer told me everything.

18:50.629 --> 18:52.464
You've hated me ever
since I supposedly

18:52.548 --> 18:54.258
destroyed his ninth
birthday party.

18:54.341 --> 18:56.093
- That might be Sawyer's
memory of his party,

18:56.176 --> 18:56.760
but mine is different.

18:56.844 --> 19:01.390
What I remember is...

19:01.473 --> 19:02.975
having a crush on you.

19:03.058 --> 19:05.060
- I'm sorry?
A what now?

19:05.144 --> 19:07.813
- OLDER CHARLIE: I didn't
know how else

19:07.896 --> 19:13.068
to tell you how I felt,
so I bought you a smoothie.

19:13.151 --> 19:16.029
Hey, Bella.
This is for you.

19:16.113 --> 19:17.239
OLDER CHARLIE:
And then I tripped.

19:17.322 --> 19:21.410
- [liquid splattering]
- KIDS: [laughing]

19:21.493 --> 19:24.204
- Do you think this
is funny--Chuckles?

19:24.288 --> 19:27.207
- Ha, ha, Chuckles.
- KIDS: [laughing]

19:27.291 --> 19:29.209
- Those guys weren't
laughing at you.

19:29.293 --> 19:30.544
They were laughing
at me.

19:30.627 --> 19:32.754
- This is the worst
party ever!

19:32.838 --> 19:34.298
I'm leaving!

19:34.381 --> 19:37.134
- But it was an accident.

19:37.217 --> 19:42.180
- KIDS: Chuckles! Chuckles!
Chuckles! Chuckles! Chuckles!

19:42.264 --> 19:45.309
- So, not only did
I get rejected,

19:45.392 --> 19:47.269
I also earned
a new nickname.

19:47.352 --> 19:50.981
Everyone called me "Chuckles"
for years after that--

19:51.064 --> 19:54.026
even my grandma.

19:54.109 --> 19:55.777
- I feel terrible.

19:55.861 --> 19:58.113
How come no one ever told
me what really happened?

19:58.196 --> 19:59.281
- I...I told Sawyer,

19:59.364 --> 20:02.159
but he kept talking
about his hot dog cake.

20:02.242 --> 20:04.328
He can't seem
to get over that.

20:04.411 --> 20:05.954
- Say no more.

20:06.038 --> 20:08.874
I'm so sorry
I yelled at you.

20:08.957 --> 20:10.292
I honestly thought you
did it on purpose

20:10.375 --> 20:12.002
because you hated me.

20:12.085 --> 20:14.796
If I knew everyone was going to
make fun of you like that,

20:14.880 --> 20:16.548
I never would have done it.

20:16.632 --> 20:18.634
- And I thought
you hated me, too.

20:18.717 --> 20:20.677
- Nope. Not any more,
at least.

20:20.761 --> 20:23.138
- Good.

20:23.221 --> 20:26.600
- Yeah. Good.

20:26.683 --> 20:28.810
- Well, if we don't
hate each other,

20:28.894 --> 20:30.854
then maybe we should
get that ice cream

20:30.938 --> 20:33.982
you were talking about
earlier--together.

20:34.066 --> 20:35.609
- You mean like a date?

20:35.692 --> 20:37.653
- Definitely
like a date.

20:37.736 --> 20:40.781
- I, uh...

20:40.864 --> 20:43.867
I mean...
[giggling coyly]

20:43.951 --> 20:46.078
- CHARLIE:
[laughing]

20:48.538 --> 20:52.876
- ♪

20:52.960 --> 20:54.336
- [sighing]

20:54.419 --> 20:56.505
Seriously, this week has been
the worst of all time.

20:56.588 --> 20:57.673
I have so much homework

20:57.756 --> 21:00.592
that my social life is
officially over until forever.

21:00.676 --> 21:02.970
Or next June.
Whichever comes first.

21:03.053 --> 21:06.390
Plus, all nine of my brothers
are grounded at the same time--

21:06.473 --> 21:07.641
even the baby.

21:07.724 --> 21:12.229
So now the air in my house
is 100 percent farts.

21:12.312 --> 21:13.897
Oh, and worst of all...

21:13.981 --> 21:16.191
my parents are going through
a brussels sprouts phase

21:16.274 --> 21:18.902
so that fart air is just...

21:18.986 --> 21:20.737
[gagging]

21:20.821 --> 21:23.240
- [Spot chirping]

21:23.323 --> 21:24.741
- Thanks for letting
me vent, Spot.

21:24.825 --> 21:27.369
I feel so much better now.
- [Spot chirping]

21:31.623 --> 21:47.431
- ♪
